    <header>
      <h2>Our History</h2>
    </header>
    <p>Back in early 2002, a friend (Nichol) and I (Daniel) were keen multiplayer gaming fans, we had just got broadband
      connections and were eager to find out what online gaming was like. After a while we found a decent game to play
      (Urban Terror, a mod for Quake 3 Arena) and started to learn it… while we were never great players, we could aim a
      gun and shoot people without problem, so we decided to take the next step and join a clan.</p>

    <p>We both joined different clans to see what they were like, the plan was for one of us to leave the worse of the
      two clans and join the better one of the two. I don’t know if this was just bad luck, or maybe fate, but both of
      the clans we joined were terrible.</p>

    <p>In one of the clans, the leaders were all about becoming uber-pro players, and winning – whatever the cost. If
      you missed a kill, rather than a “never mind, you’ll do better next time” message, all you would get was an
      insult, and an order to do better. The other clan was just as bad with lots of people cheating and generally being
      very nasty and difficult, both to the teams they played against, as well as each other.</p>

    <p>We decided that enough was enough, and together planed to form our own clan, a clan that would be different to
      the rest, a clan that would do things right, a clan that would follow our ethics and ensure that everyone had a
      good time while playing.</p>

    <h3>Where did the name come from?</h3>

    <p>The name
      <em>Fight Club Monkey</em> came from a brainstorming session between Nichol and I. Although I can't remember any
      of the other names we came up with, I do know the final choice was inspired both by the film Fight Club, and the
      <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xyoGDAjd0eA">ITV digital adverts featuring Johnny Vegas and his
        pet/sidekick monkey &#8211; Monkeh</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
