    <header>
      <h2>Currently Playing</h2>
    </header>
    <p>Unlike traditional gaming guilds and clans, which focus on a single game, and aim to be the best at it with
      military planning and precision, we’re a far more relaxed outfit, which believe in gaming for fun. As a result of
      this, we’ll often have a couple of different ‘official’ games going at a time.</p>

    <h3><em>Monkeys and Demons</em> – Guild Wars 2</h3>

    <p>Guild Wars 2 (GW2) is a massively multiplayer online role-playing game in development by ArenaNet. Set in the
      fantasy world of Tyria, the game follows the re-emergence of Destiny’s Edge, a disbanded guild dedicated to
      fighting the Elder Dragons, a Lovecraftian species that has seized control of Tyria in the time since the original
      Guild Wars.</p>

    <p>As a guild, the majority of our players play on the <strong>Vabbi</strong> EU server, on which we’re hoping to
      strike up a presence, although players on other servers can still join. We don’t actively recruit new
      members, but we’re always willing to entertain applications. The guild name <strong>Monkeys and Demons</strong>
      (<em><strong>[MaD]</strong>)</em> was inspired by the book and film <em>Angels and Demons</em> by Dan Brown.</p>

    <h3><em>Mineclub Monkey</em> - Minecraft</h3>

    <p>Minecraft (MC) is the indie game that was a huge success before it even got an official released. Created by
      Markus Persson (aka, Notch), MC is focused on creativity and building, allowing players to build constructions out
      of textured cubes in a 3D world by acquire resources while maintaining their health and hunger, and fending off
      attacks from Creepers and other night-time nasties.</p>

    <p>As a clan we run our own Minecraft server. In world, we have a communal hub called <em>Monkey Island</em>, which
      we use as a central location for players to share resources, helping create the healthy community spirit that we
      like.</p>
